{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"DeviceMotionEvent()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/DeviceMotionEvent","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><svg class=\"icon icon-nonstandard\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-nonstandard\"></use>\n</svg><em><code>DeviceMotionEvent()</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/acceleration\"><code>acceleration</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/accelerationIncludingGravity\"><code>accelerationIncludingGravity</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/interval\"><code>interval</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/rotationRate\"><code>rotationRate</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Device Orientation Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventAcceleration\"><code>DeviceAcceleration</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent\"><code>DeviceOrientationEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventRotationRate\"><code>DeviceRotationRate</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard warning\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Non-standard:</strong> This feature is non-standard and is not on a standards track. Do not use it on production sites facing the Web: it will not work for every user. There may also be large incompatibilities between implementations and the behavior may change in the future.</p></div>\n<p>\n  The <strong><code>DeviceMotionEvent()</code></strong> constructor creates a new\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent</code></a>.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">DeviceMotionEvent</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>type<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">DeviceMotionEvent</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>type<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> options<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"type\"><code>type</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMString\"><code>DOMString</code></a> representing the name of the event.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"options\"><code>options</code><span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Options are as follows:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>\n        <code>acceleration</code>: An object giving the acceleration of the device on\n        the three axis X, Y and Z. Acceleration is expressed in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meter_per_second_squared\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">m/s²</a>.\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <code>accelerationIncludingGravity</code>: An object giving the acceleration of\n        the device on the three axis X, Y and Z with the effect of gravity. Acceleration\n        is expressed in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meter_per_second_squared\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">m/s²</a>.\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <code>rotationRate</code>: An object giving the rate of change of the device's\n        orientation on the three orientation axis alpha, beta and gamma. Rotation rate is\n        express in degrees per seconds.\n      </li>\n      <li>\n        <code>interval</code>: A number representing the interval of time, in\n        milliseconds, at which data is obtained from the device.\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specifications","title":"Specifications","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>Not part of any specifications.</em></p>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.DeviceMotionEvent.DeviceMotionEvent","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/DeviceMotionEvent/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The DeviceMotionEvent() constructor creates a new\n  DeviceMotionEvent.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-03-22T06:55:31.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"DeviceMotionEvent.DeviceMotionEvent()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"DeviceMotionEvent.DeviceMotionEvent()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder"